{"id": "1408448260133224599", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "content": "<@1376763322568937562> one question regarding the updated source sheets that has all languages - how should we handle the .csv uploads for our languages now that there are multiple languages in every line?\n\nRight now, the process is to only edit the column for the language we are working on. However, now that the sheet has columns for other languages, I fear that including them will revert the work that other translators are doing by overwriting their edited translation with the original default MTL text. Should we remove columns for the other languages, or has this already been accounted for?", "timestamp": "2025-08-22T13:50:32.919000+00:00", "mentions": ["1376763322568937562"]}
{"id": "1408449547054612620", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "193751134840684544", "author_name": "valoup", "content": "Sharing Goz's previous contribution because it also helped me visualize https://github.com/Goz-0/Morimens-Localizations/blob/main/TRANSLATIONS/01_UPLOAD_YOUR_CONTRIBUTIONS/en/EN_Gameplay_Proofreading.csv\n\nYou keep the Key, ShortKey, Source, Row... CN and then your Translation while deleting the other language, you should also keep only the lines you edited, meaning if you worked on 10 different lines, you should only upload those", "timestamp": "2025-08-22T13:55:39.745000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-22T13:56:04.350000+00:00", "embeds": [{"type": "article", "title": "Morimens-Localizations/TRANSLATIONS/01_UPLOAD_YOUR_CONTRIBUTIONS/en...", "url": "https://github.com/Goz-0/Morimens-Localizations/blob/main/TRANSLATIONS/01_UPLOAD_YOUR_CONTRIBUTIONS/en/EN_Gameplay_Proofreading.csv", "description": "Contribute to Goz-0/Morimens-Localizations development by creating an account on GitHub."}]}
